adding-bottom:16px;padding-left:0;padding-right:0;text-align:left;width:688px;\">\n<table style=\"border-collapse:collapse;border-spacing:0;padding:0;text-align:left;vertical-align:top;width:100%;\"><tr style=\"padding:0;text-align:left;vertical-align:top;\"><th style=\"margin:0;color:#43414E;font-family:Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif;font-size:16px;font-weight:400;line-height:1.4;padding:0;text-align:left;\"><img style=\"clear:both;max-height:16px;max-width:82px;text-decoration:none;width:auto;\" width=\"82\" height=\"16\" src=\"https://kinsta.com/assets/emails/logo-166x34.png\" alt=\"logo-166x34.png\" /></th>\n<th class=\"ex-expander\" style=\"margin:0;color:#43414E;font-family:Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif;font-size:16px;font-weight:400;line-height:1.4;padding:0;text-align:left;width:0;\"></th>\n</tr></table></th>\n</tr></tbody></table></td>\n</tr></tbody></table></td>\n</tr></table><table align=\"center\" class=\"ex-wrapper ex-faux-box ex-float-center\" style=\"margin:0 auto;background:#491FD7;border-collapse:collapse;border-spacing:0;float:none;padding:0;text-align:center;vertical-align:top;width:100%;\"><tr style=\"padding:0;text-align:left;vertical-align:top;\"><td class=\"ex-wrapper-inner\" style=\"margin:0;border-collapse:collapse;color:#43414E;font-family:Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif;font-size:16px;font-weight:400;line-height:1.4;padding:0;text-align:left;vertical-align:top;\">\n<table style=\"margin:0 auto;background:#fff;border:1px solid #EAEAEA;border-bottom:0;border-collapse:collapse;border-spacing:0;padding:0;text-align:inherit;vertical-align:top;width:680px;\" align=\"center\" class=\"ex-container\"><tbody><tr style=\"padding:0;text-align:left;vertical-align:top;\"><td style=\"margin:0;border-collapse:collapse;color:#43414E;font-family:Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif;font-size:16px;font-weight:400;line-height:1.4;padding:0;text-align:left;vertical-align:top;\">\n<table class=\"ex-spacer\" style=\"border-collapse:collapse;border-spacing:0;padding:0;text-align:left;vertical-align:top;width:100%;\"><tbody><tr style=\"padding:0;text-align:left;vertical-align:top;\"><td height=\"40\" style=\"margin:0;border-collapse:collapse;color:#43414E;font-family:Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif;font-size:40px;font-weight:400;line-height:40px;padding:0;text-align:left;vertical-align:top;\"> </td>\n</tr></tbody></table></td>\n</tr></tbody></table></td>\n</tr></table><table align=\"center\" class=\"ex-container ex-float-center\" style=\"margin:0 auto;background:#fefefe;border-collapse:collapse;border-spacing:0;float:none;padding:0;text-align:center;vertical-align:top;width:680px;\"><tbody><tr style=\"padding:0;text-align:left;vertical-align:top;\"><td style=\"margin:0;border-collapse:collapse;color:#43414E;font-family:Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif;font-size:16px;font-weight:400;line-height:1.4;padding:0;text-align:left;vertical-align:top;\">\n<table class=\"ex-row\" style=\"border-collapse:collapse;border-spacing:0;padding:0;text-align:left;vertical-align:top;width:100%;\"><tbody><tr style=\"padding:0;text-align:left;vertical-align:top;\"><th class=\"ex-bordered ex-border-no-top ex-small-12 ex-large-12 ex-columns ex-first ex-last\" style=\"margin:0 auto;border:1px solid #EAEAEA;border-top:0;color:#43414E;font-family:Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif;font-size:16px;font-weight:400;line-height:1.4;padding:0;padding-bottom:16px;padding-left:16px;padding-right:16px;text-align:left;width:664px;\">\n<table style=\"border-collapse:collapse;border-spacing:0;padding:0;text-align:left;vertical-align:top;width:100%;\"><tr style=\"padding:0;text-align:left;vertical-align:top;\"><th style=\"margin:0;color:#43414E;font-family:Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif;font-size:16px;font-weight:400;line-height:1.4;padding:0;text-align:left;\">\n<div class=\"ex-content\" style=\"padding-left:50px;padding-right:50px;\">\n<h1 style=\"margin-top:0px;\">Hi WP Perk,</h1>\n<p>We're writing to let you know about an upcoming change that affects SSL certificate renewal.</p>\n<p>Wildcard SSL certificate renewals will now require adding or updating a DNS TXT record when you renew a certificate (most SSL certificates renew annually). The DNS TXT record is unique for each domain and will change every time the certificate renews.</p>\n<p><em>\"Wildcard\" SSL certificates are those that automatically cover any subdomains you might use. In most cases, the wildcard is indicated by an asterisk: *.domain.com.</em></p>\n<br><h2>Are You Affected?</h2>\n<p>All SSL certificates are affected by the change. But the good news is you may not have to take any action. Here's the breakdown:</p>\n<ul><li>If you <strong>use a certificate provided by Kinsta AND use Kinsta DNS, you don't need to take any action</strong>. Your certificates will be automatically validated when they renew.</li>\n<li style=\"list-style:none;\"><br></li>\n<li>If you <strong>use a certificate provided by Kinsta but do NOT use Kinsta DNS, you will be required to validate your SSL certificates</strong> with a DNS TXT record when your certificates renew.</li>\n<li style=\"list-style:none;\"><br></li>\n<li><strong>If you purchased a certificate from a third-party SSL vendor</strong> and installed it on your Kinsta site, <strong>you <em>may</em> be required to validate your SSL certificates</strong> with a DNS TXT record when your certificates renew. <em>To find out whether the DNS TXT record is required, contact your SSL provider.</em></li>\n<li style=\"list-style:none;\"><br></li>\n<li>At the moment, all certificates provided by Kinsta are wildcard certificates. But soon we will offer non-wildcard certificates as well. <strong>When you use one of the upcoming non-wildcard SSL certificates provided by Kinsta, you won't need to do any manual validation</strong>. Your certificates will be automatically validated when they renew.</li>\n</ul><br><h2>This Is an Industry-wide Change</h2>\n<p>While Cloudflare (and by extension, Kinsta) requires TXT record validation for wildcard domains, we're not alone. It's becoming the standard across the entire SSL certificate industry. Ultimately, this will affect <em>all</em> wildcard certificates, regardless of where they were obtained or where the domains are hosted.</p>\n<br><h2>Let Us Worry About the Details for You</h2>\n<p>Remember, you can avoid the necessity of any manual intervention by using the Kinsta-provided certificate along with Kinsta DNS.</p>\n<br><p>We understand that this adds another annual task to many of our to-do lists. But the goal is to increase SSL certificate security, and that increases your website security!</p>\n<p>If you have any questions, please open a chat with one of our support team members. We're available around the clock and always happy to help.</p>\n</div>\n</th>\n<th class=\"ex-expander\" style=\"margin:0;color:#43414E;font-family:Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif;font-size:16px;font-weight:400;line-height:1.4;padding:0;text-align:left;width:0;\"></th>\n</tr></table></th>\n</tr></tbody></table><table class=\"ex-row\" style=\"border-collapse:collapse;border-spacing:0;padding:0;text-align:left;vertical-align:top;width:100%;\"><tbody><tr style=\"padding:0;text-align:left;vertical-align:top;\"><th class=\"ex-small-12 ex-large-12 ex-columns ex-first ex-last\" style=\"margin:0 auto;color:#43414E;font-family:Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif;font-size:16px;font-weight:400;line-height:1.4;padding:0;padding-bottom:16px;padding-left:16px;padding-right:16px;text-align:left;width:664px;\">\n<table style=\"border-collapse:collapse;border-spacing:0;padding:0;text-align:left;vertical-align:top;width:100%;\"><tr style=\"padding:0;text-align:left;vertical-align:top;\"><th style=\"margin:0;color:#43414E;font-family:Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif;font-size:16px;font-weight:400;line-height:1.4;padding:0;text-align:left;\">\n<table class=\"ex-spacer\" style=\"border-collapse:collapse;border-spacing:0;padding:0;text-align:left;vertical-align:top;width:100%;\"><tbody><tr style=\"padding:0;text-align:left;vertical-ali